Fixed the diagnostics error channel so `reply.statusCode` reflects Fastify’s resolved error status before the `tracing:fastify.request.handler:error` event is published.

What changed:
- Added `lib/error-status-code.js` to centralize Fastify’s error-status resolution.
- Applied that status resolution before diagnostics `error` publishes in:
  - `lib/handle-request.js`
  - `lib/wrap-thenable.js`
- Reused the same helper from `lib/error-handler.js` so diagnostics and actual error handling stay aligned.
- Added a regression test for the nested custom error-handler case in `test/diagnostics-channel/error-status.test.js`.

Why this fixes it:
- The diagnostics event was firing before Fastify had derived the fallback error status, so `reply.statusCode` was still `200`.
- Now Fastify resolves the status first, then publishes the diagnostics event.

Verification:
- `node --test test/diagnostics-channel/error-status.test.js`
- `npm test`

